    <!-- OBJECT -->
    <div id="object">
        <h2>OBJECT:</h2>
        <div class="rules-box">
            <ul>
                <li>This new Rulebook allows you to convert your Soloverse Game into a Deck-Builder Style Game.</li>
                <li>For the uninitiated Deck-Builders have Players:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Start the Game with identical copies of a Personal Deck of usually around 10 Cards, comprising of Currency and either Attack or Victory Point Cards [depending on the Deck-Building Game’s winning condition].</li>
                        <li>You then use your Personal Deck to upgrade it by buying higher grade Currency and Attack/Victory Point Cards.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>This is a 2-6 Player Game Mode, where You will each Setup a Level Up Deck [comprised of Chaos Draw Cards] & take a Personal Coloured Half-Deck, while racing each other to reach either: the Chaos Draw +5 [Level 5] or Optionally, the Chaos Draw +10 Specific Targeted [Level 7]! Do so and Win!!</li>
                <li>As such this Game Mode is for those wanting even more of a challenge from Soloverse, with an extended Game Setup…</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <a href="#top" class="shortcut-link">🔝 Return to Index Matrix</a>
    </div>

    <!-- SETUP -->
    <div id="setup">
        <h2>SETUP:</h2>
        <div class="rules-box">
            <ol>
                <li>To begin with, Decide on the Victory Condition, either:
                    <ol type="a">
                        <li><strong>SHORTER GAME:</strong> The First to reach Their Random Chaos Draw +5.</li>
                        <li><strong>LONGER GAME:</strong> Or the First to reach the Chaos Draw +10 Specific Targeted.</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>Then choose which Optional Expansions will be used in the Game [compare Universal Game Notes: First Play Recommendations].
                    <div class="note-box">
                        <strong>NOTE:</strong> If you have added any Optional Expansions, check if they have any Additional Setup Rules.
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>As a group, help separate from the Deck:
                    <ol type="a">
                        <li>Each Coloured Set of Cards [separately from each other].</li>
                        <li>All Chaos Draw Effect Cards, further separating them into Their values [+2, +3, +4 and +5], combining all versions of said values together [Normal, Skip, Reverse and Specific Targeted].</li>
                        <li>All other Chaos Cards.</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>Now Shuffle each Pile of Chaos Draw Effect Value Cards individually, and setup each Player’s Level Up Deck, Dealing these Cards Face-Down to all Players:
                    <ol type="a">
                        <li>Deal a Random Chaos Draw +5 Chaos Card.</li>
                        <li>On top of that Card, Deal a Random Chaos Draw +4 Chaos Card.</li>
                        <li>On top of that Card, Deal a Random Chaos Draw +3 Chaos Card.</li>
                        <li>On top of that Card, Deal a Random Chaos Draw +2 Chaos Card.</li>
                    </ol>
                    <div class="note-box">
                        <strong>NOTE:</strong> This Deck will be accessed in order from top to bottom as You Gain Them and Level Up Your Deck.
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>Now each Player chooses a Colour for themselves, and further separates it into 2 Coloured Half-Decks [so 2 Piles with 1 copy of each Coloured Card (0-9, Reverse, Skip and Draw +2) ]:
                    <ol type="a">
                        <li>One Pile becomes the Player’s Personal Deck.
                            <ol type="i">
                                <li>Separate and keep the <span style="color: var(--color-link);">Coloured Draw +2</span> and place Face-Down to start Your Personal Deck.</li>
                                <li>Then Shuffle the rest of Your Personal Deck and place it Face-Down on top of the <span style="color: var(--color-link);">Coloured Draw +2</span>.</li>
                                <li>Now leave room for 3 Piles in front of You:
                                    <ol>
                                        <li>Your Level Up Deck.</li>
                                        <li>Your Personal Deck.</li>
                                        <li>Your Discards [to be added].</li>
                                    </ol>
                                </li>
                            </ol>
                        </li>
                        <li>Now take Your Spare Coloured Half-Deck and Remove the following Action Class Cards: <span style="color: var(--color-link);">Draw +2</span>, <span style="color: var(--color-link);">Reverse</span> and <span style="color: var(--color-link);">Skip</span>, and add the Numbered Cards left [0-9] to the Tier 1 Trade Deck together with all the other Players’ spare Coloured Half-Decks and Shuffle it thoroughly; placing it at the bottom Right of the Play Area.</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>From the Remaining Colours in Your Game Box, add 1 spare Coloured Half-Deck’s Number Cards [0-9] to the remaining Chaos Cards left and form a Deck.</li>
                <li>Shuffle this Deck, then Separate it into 3 Piles [as equally sized as possible], creating 3 separate Tiered Trade Decks; and place each Deck in a column above the Tier 1 Trade Deck.
                    <ul>
                        <li>Now the Trade Decks will be Tiered 1-4 from the Bottom to the Top of the column.</li>
                        <li>These Tiered Trade Decks will have Randomised Contents, but Their Costs will be Preset [for better or worse!].</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Reveal 4 Cards from each Trade Deck from Tiers 2-4 to create 3 Trade Rows, one above each other on the Left of each Tiered Trade Deck.</li>
                <li>Shuffle and place the 3 Random Chaos Draw +10’s Face-Down separately above Tier 4 Trade Row. And finally, above the Tier 4 Trade Deck, place the Chaos Draw +10 Specific Targeted Face-Up.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>

