    <!-- HOW TO PLAY -->
    <div id="how-to-play">
        <h2>HOW TO PLAY:</h2>
        <div class="rules-box">
            <ol>
                <li>Determine who goes First, then each Player Draws 5 Cards.</li>
                <li>Next, reveal 1 Card from the Tier 1 Trade Deck for each Player in the Game, forming the last, Tier 1 Trade Row.
                    <div class="note-box">
                        <strong>NOTE:</strong> Now from Left to Right-Top to Bottom, Your setup should have a Grid of 4 Trade Rows, then 4 Tiered Trade Decks, then the Chaos Draw +10ST Face-Up with the 3 Random Chaos Draw +10’s Face-Down underneath it.
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>On Your Turn, play Cards from your Hand in front of you. Once this is done, you cannot put it back in your Hand.
                    <ol type="a">
                        <li><strong>0-9 Coloured Number Cards [XP]</strong> allows you to Buy Cards in the various Tiered Trade Rows based on the following Costs:
                            <ol type="i">
                                <li><strong>Tier 1:</strong> A minimum XP of the Face Value of the Numbered Card shown.
                                    <br><br><strong>ADVANCED OPTIONAL RULES:</strong> Use just one of these or both for an increased challenge.
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>Tier 1 Trade Row XP Cards that match Your chosen Personal Deck’s Colour are 2XP cheaper for Yourself.</li>
                                        <li>Tier 1 Trade Row XP Cards that do NOT match Your chosen Personal Deck’s Colour are 2XP more expensive for Yourself.</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </li>
                                <li><strong>Tier 2:</strong> 3XP.</li>
                                <li><strong>Tier 3:</strong> 5XP + Discard Any 1 Chaos Card.</li>
                                <li><strong>Tier 4:</strong> 7XP + Discard Any 2 Chaos Cards.</li>
                            </ol>
                            <p><strong>NOTES:</strong></p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Unless otherwise stated, any Cards Purchased [including if Purchased for Free], must be placed in your Discards.</li>
                                <li>If, after Purchasing a Card from Tier 1-3 Trade Decks, you reveal a Trap Class Chaos Card, resolve its Effects then Scrap it.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <strong>IMPORTANT COST RESTRICTION:</strong> There are no Refunds. Once an XP Card is used to Buy a Card from any Trade Row, that Card can no longer be used that Turn.
                            <br><br><strong>EXAMPLE:</strong> You Play 3 & 4 XP Cards and buy a Card worth 5 XP. Those XP Cards are now considered Used and Cannot be used towards other Purchases.
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>0 XP Card:</strong> Allows you to Scrap any Card in Your Discards. Potentially Strengthening Your Personal Deck, making it easier to Draw the Cards You need.</li>
                        <li><strong>Reverse Action Class Card:</strong> Reverses Play. Then Forces all other Players to Discard 1 Card [Hand and/or Table] immediately.
                            <br><br><strong>PLAY TESTING NOTE:</strong> Reverse and similar Effects always activate before Effects similar to Skip.
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Skip Action Class Card:</strong> Skips the next Player’s Turn. They Discard Their Hand and Redraw. Then allows You to Draw 1 Card and set it aside until the Start of Your next Turn.
                            <br><br><strong>PLAY TESTING NOTE:</strong> If playing more than 1 Skip Effect, They do not Stack on that Target but continues to Skip each subsequent Player instead.
                            <br><br><strong>EXAMPLE:</strong> You Play 2 Skip Effect Cards, Skipping the next 2 Players’ Turns.
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Draw +2 Action Class Card:</strong> Allows you to Draw 2 Cards this Turn.</li>
                        <li><strong>Chaos Cards:</strong> Follow their Effects based on the (09-A) Soloverse - Deck-Builder (Definitions Rulebook).</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>You will also need to Level Up Your Personal Deck to Win:
                    <br><br>
                    <strong>LV1:</strong> You Start on LV1 with your Coloured Draw +2.
                    <br><br>
                    <strong>LV2:</strong> On any Turn You have in Your Hand:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Your Coloured Draw +2 to Play.</li>
                        <li>A minimum of 4XP to Play.</li>
                        <li>Plus, any 1 Chaos Card to Discard.</li>
                    </ul>
                    You may Purchase Your Random Chaos Draw +2 and add it to Your Discards.
                    <br><br>
                    <strong>LV3:</strong> On any Turn You have in Your Hand:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Your Random Draw +2 to Play.</li>
                        <li>A minimum of 6XP to Play.</li>
                        <li>Plus, any 1 Chaos Card to Discard.</li>
                    </ul>
                    You may Purchase Your Random Chaos Draw +3 and add it to Your Discards.
                    <br><br>
                    <strong>LV4:</strong> On any Turn You have in Your Hand:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Your Random Draw +3 to Play.</li>
                        <li>A minimum of 8XP to Play.</li>
                        <li>Plus, any 1 Chaos Card to Discard.</li>
                    </ul>
                    You may Purchase Your Random Chaos Draw +4 and add it to Your Discards.
                    <br><br>
                    <strong>LV5:</strong> On any Turn You have in Your Hand:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Your Random Draw +4 to Play.</li>
                        <li>A minimum of 10XP to Play.</li>
                        <li>Plus, any 1 Chaos Card to Discard.</li>
                    </ul>
                    You may Purchase Your Random Chaos Draw +5 and add it to Your Discards. This CAN Win You the Game if this Victory Condition was chosen at the Start of the Game. If NOT, Continue with the following:
                    <br><br>
                    <strong>LV6:</strong> On any Turn You have in Your Hand:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Your Random Draw +5 to Play.</li>
                        <li>A minimum of 20XP to Play.</li>
                        <li>Plus, any 1 Chaos Card to Discard.</li>
                    </ul>
                    You may Purchase a Random Chaos Draw +10 from the Table and add it to Your Discards.
                    <div class="note-box">
                        <strong>NOTE:</strong> If Playing with more than 3 Players, once the last Random Chaos Draw +10 is Gained, all other Players instantly Lose.
                    </div>
                    <strong>LV7:</strong> On any Turn You have in Your Hand:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Your Random Draw +10 to Play.</li>
                        <li>A minimum of 20XP to Play.</li>
                        <li>Plus, any 2 Chaos Cards to Discard.</li>
                    </ul>
                    You may Purchase the Winning Chaos Draw +10 Specific Targeted and add it to Your Discards.
                </li>
                <li>Once any chosen Cards have been Played and their Effects finalised, placed any Cards left in your Hand and those you Played into your Discards and Draw 5 more Cards</li>
                <li>When You need to continue Drawing and Your Personal Deck is empty, Shuffle Your Discards to re-form your Personal Deck.</li>
                <li>Then end your Turn.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
        <a href="#top" class="shortcut-link">🔝 Return to Index Matrix</a>
    </div>

    <!-- VICTORY CONDITIONS -->
    <div id="victory-conditions">
        <h2>VICTORY CONDITIONS:</h2>
        <div class="rules-box">
            <ol>
                <li>Obtaining either the Chaos Draw +5 or the Chaos Draw +10 Specific Targeted [depending on Your choice at the Start of the Game] Wins You the Game!</li>
                <li>Special Victory Conditions.
                    <ol type="a">
                        <li>Some Expansions have Special Victory Conditions that exceed the normal means of Winning. For example:
                            <ul>
                                <li>The Singularity Expansion allows you to collect all 3 Unification Class Chaos Cards.</li>
                                <li>While the Crisis Expansion “Crisis Class” Chaos Cards allow for many different Special Victory Conditions.</li>
                            </ul>
                            In any of these situations, doing so automatically, and instantly, Wins you the game!
                        </li>
                        <li>The game ends Without a Clear Winner [such as all Tiered Trade Rows run out of Gainable Cards]. In any situation without a clear Winner:
                            <ol type="i">
                                <li>The Player with the Highest Levelled Personal Deck Wins.</li>
                                <li>If Players have an Equal Personal Deck Level, the Player with the Highest Total of Chaos Cards in Their Personal Deck Wins.</li>
                                <li>If Players have an Equal amount of Chaos Cards in Their Personal Deck, the Player with the Highest Total XP in Their Personal Deck Wins.</li>
                                <li>If Players have an Equal Total XP left in Their Personal Decks, Congrats! It must have been a Great Game!! All remaining Players separate Their Level Up Deck [Coloured Draw +2 to Random Chaos Draw +5], Shuffle them and reveal the Top Card at the same time. The Player with the Highest Value Draw Card Wins!</li>
                                <li>If that’s still not enough, repeat the process until you find a Winner [I mean, at this point, you must be desperate].</li>
                            </ol>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>
        <a href="#top" class="shortcut-link">🔝 Return to Index Matrix</a>
    </div>

    <!-- Soloverse Rulebook Page Engine: Auto-Theme Detection & Update Sync -->
    <script is:inline>
        (function() {
            // 1. SERVICE WORKER REVALIDATION
            if ('serviceWorker' in navigator) {
                navigator.serviceWorker.getRegistrations().then(function(registrations) {
                    for (let registration of registrations) {
                        registration.update(); 
                    }
                });
            }

            // 2. AUTOMATED THEME EVALUATION (User Override vs System Preference)
            const savedTheme = localStorage.getItem('soloverse-theme');
            const devicePrefersDarkMode = window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches;
            
            let activeTheme = 'dark'; // Base anchor default fallback

            if (savedTheme) {
                // Priority 1: Respect explicit button clicks from the main bookshelf hub
                activeTheme = savedTheme;
            } else {
                // Priority 2: Auto-adopt the tablet/device's native operating system mode
                activeTheme = devicePrefersDarkMode ? 'dark' : 'light';
            }

            // Mount theme instantly to root document element
            document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', activeTheme);

			// 3. MANUAL CANVAS ROTATION OVERRIDE CONTROLS
            window.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
                const rotateBtn = document.getElementById('rotate-view-btn');
                if (!rotateBtn) return;

                let currentRotateState = localStorage.getItem('soloverse-rotate-lock') || 'portrait';
                document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-rotate-override', currentRotateState);

                rotateBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
                    const activeState = document.documentElement.getAttribute('data-rotate-override');
                    const targetState = activeState === 'landscape' ? 'portrait' : 'landscape';
                    
                    document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-rotate-override', targetState);
                    localStorage.setItem('soloverse-rotate-lock', targetState);
                });
            });
        })();
    </script>
